    <text type="letter">
        <body>         
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.02085_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1876-04-23">April 23d /76</date>
                        <name type="place">140 East 38th st</name>
                        <name type="place">New York<ptr target="loc.01981_n1"/></name>
                </dateline>
                
                <salute>My dear Mr Whitman:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Your note<ptr target="loc.01981_n3"/> was received and I am only waiting until the 1st of May when I shall 
                be more "flush" to send you an order for five copies of your complete works.</p>
            <p>I am glad that you are publishing works in this complete form, and feel sure 
                that you will be well repaid in every way for the effort</p>
            <p>I hope to do more than this in the way of getting subscribers.</p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>Very sincerely Yours</salute>
                <signed>J.Q.A. <hi rend="underline">Ward</hi></signed>
            </closer>    
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.02086_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.02087_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="left">friendly note from Ward, the sculptor (will send an order &#38; money after May 1)</note>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ht" place="top">see notes Sept 7 1888</note>
